# Plan Review: core_engine_plan_v3.md
Date: 2026-03-22
Reviewer: Plan Reviewer Agent

## Summary

The plan is well-structured, TDD-disciplined, and covers the full Task 17 spec: ring buffer design,
keying rules, timing gate, STATUS extension, and on_raw exclusion. The Project State at Plan Time
section is present and accurate. The LatencyStats implementation and percentile formula match the
spec exactly. However, two CRITICAL defects were found that will cause GREEN steps to fail.

Issue 1: test_latency_stats_n_samples_sorted contains a dead double-assert (== 5 then == 6) that
permanently blocks the Task 2 GREEN step — the first assertion is wrong per the spec formula.

Issue 2: test_module_config_metrics_enabled_default uses a bare relative path for the TOML file.
All existing config tests use _ROOT = Path(__file__).parents[2] for this reason (Task 10 fix,
commit 80b5a1f). The test will raise FileNotFoundError outside the project root.

## Issues

[CRITICAL] Task 2, Step 1 — test_latency_stats_n_samples_sorted contains stale double-assert
The test first asserts s.percentile(0.50) == 5 (wrong), then asserts s.percentile(0.50) == 6
(correct). Spec formula: values[min(int(0.50 * 10), 9)] = values[5] = 6 (sorted [1..10]).
The wrong == 5 assertion executes first and raises AssertionError even with a correct
implementation. Remove the == 5 assertion entirely; keep only == 6.

[CRITICAL] Task 3, Step 1 — test_module_config_metrics_enabled_default uses relative path
ModuleConfig.from_file("config/modules/example_strategy.toml") will raise FileNotFoundError
when pytest is not run from the project root. Existing tests use
_ROOT = Path(__file__).parents[2] at module scope. Fix: use
ModuleConfig.from_file(str(_ROOT / "config" / "modules" / "example_strategy.toml")).

[MINOR] Task 4, Step 2 — expected RED failure message is inaccurate
Plan says "AttributeError: type object '_MetricsMod' has no attribute 'metrics_enabled'".
_MetricsMod sets metrics_enabled = True as a class attr, so that resolves fine. Actual
failure will be "AttributeError: '_MetricsMod' object has no attribute '_latency'".
Non-blocking but should be corrected for implementer clarity.

